                              or of the <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7840Phanuel">Archangel Phanuel</persName>, cp. for example,
                            <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/PGNHK2VR"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Mercier1997Art"/><title level="m">Art that Heals: the Image as Medicine in Ethiopia</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Jacques</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Mercier</t:surname></author><pubPlace>New York, NY</pubPlace><publisher>Prestel–The Museum for African Art</publisher><date>1997</date><citedRange>80</citedRange></bibl>.</desc>
                          </decoNote>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d2" type="ornamentation">
                            <desc>Ornamental band in black and red between <ref target="#ms_i1"/> and <ref target="#ms_i2"/>.</desc>
                          </decoNote>
