                            <desc>Drawing of a face with horns (?) in black and red between
                              <ref target="#ms_i2"/> and <ref target="#ms_i3"/></desc>
                          </decoNote>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d4" type="drawing">
                            <desc>Drawing of a face inside a square in black and red between
                              <ref target="#ms_i3"/> and <ref target="#ms_i4"/>, possibly an image of a cherub. Cp for example,
                            <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/PGNHK2VR"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Mercier1997Art"/><title level="m">Art that Heals: the Image as Medicine in Ethiopia</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Jacques</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Mercier</t:surname></author><pubPlace>New York, NY</pubPlace><publisher>Prestel–The Museum for African Art</publisher><date>1997</date><citedRange>88</citedRange></bibl>.</desc>
